Subject: RE: Pending DASR's for Existing Enron Customers
Importance: High


Matt,

I thought I'd respond for Diann.  The decision is pretty clear on this.  As you recall, the issue was raised by UC/CSU who specifically mentioned that the utilities were unilaterally setting deadlines for submission of customer names and DASRs. Let me quote:

Section F, p. 19:

"In its rehearing application, UC/CSU seek clarification on whether D.01-09-060's prohibition of any new contracts for direct access services after September 20, 2001, allows or requires utilities to refuse to process DASRs for an account under a pre-September 20 contract."

p.20:

"We reaffirm that for the time being, and unless the Commission states otherwise in a subsequent decision, utilities are required to process DASRs relating to contracts or agreements that were executed on or before September 20, 2001, including DASRs for service to new facilities or accounts if the underlying contract pursuant to which those DASRs are submitted allowed for the provision of that additional service."

p.21

"For purpose of utility compliance with D.01-09-060, we want to make it clear that, unless otherwise directed or allowed to in a subsequent Commission decision, utilities cannot set a deadline after which they could refuse to process DASRs relating to contracts excuted on or before September 20, 2001."

Matt, these are just the highlights.  The Decision has more language providing additional clarity.  By the way, this decision was mailed on October 12 -- after your October 5 deadline. I think the Decision is crystal clear.  You must accept all DASRs for contracts signed on or before September 20 and you cannot set artificial deadlines after which you will not accept those DASRs.

So, given the above.  Can you please explain your position?

Regarding the Novemver 1 date -- you may remember the Rule 22 meeting held by the utilities, ESPs and customers in eaarly October.  The ESPs agreed to make a good faith effort to provide a complete customer list by November 1, with the understanding that additional names and facilities could be added later with some verification process to ensure the DA contract was signed on or before September 20.  We agreed to do this to help the utilities meet their obligations under D. 01-09-060.  Enron has met that commitment. 

Sue Mara
